{
  "stem": "3097.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, they didn't come back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't make-- physically they didn't make it smaller.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there were about 28,000 people there, and maybe the-- the population could be accepted, maybe 1/10 of it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It were very, very crowded, you see?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "For example, like from our-- we had six people-- two people there in the kitchen, and our four people in one room, in our simple two room.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, a room and a kitchen-- we used to live.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But this, we stayed there until August the 20th, 1942.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I-- I listen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Before Treblinka, I knew there's-- we have-- we had a desperate situation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The situation was desperate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never expected the Germans to be that strong.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I could see, because the railroad was going not far from our place in ghetto, I saw what they-- what they prepared themselves for Russia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I see all the tanks and all the guns that they carried, you see, towards Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because there was Krakow, Warsaw, you see, the railroads, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when they attacked Russia, they started to go east so rapidly and take-- took so many armies-- destroyed so many armies, destroyed so many, and took prisoners, us prisoners.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I thought that they will never be destroyed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I thought they would never let-- that nobody will be able to help us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when I started to make contact, already at that time, my uncle, who used to be an officer in-- in the Polish army before the war, he had some contact.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and his brother-in-law, who was a member with him of [NON-ENGLISH], the-- you know-- they were revisionists, you know, from [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They organized in my area a group of Jewish people who were revisionists.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
